    slug: "islam-atotal-beginners-guide-2",
    description: `Islam: A Total Beginner's Guide is a clear, comprehensive, and welcoming English-language introduction to the religion of Islam, designed specifically for readers who have little or no prior knowledge of Islamic beliefs, practices, and history. Written with the non-Muslim reader in mind as well as new converts seeking a solid foundation in their faith, this book presents the essential teachings of Islam in a manner that is accessible, accurate, and free from unnecessary technical jargon, while maintaining the respect and seriousness that a discussion of religious beliefs deserves. The book is structured in a logical progression that mirrors the natural journey of someone encountering Islam for the first time. It begins with the foundational concept of Islam itself — the meaning of the word (submission to the will of Allah), the central figure of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) as the final messenger of God, and the holy book of the Quran as the literal word of Allah preserved in its original form. The chapter on the six articles of faith (iman) explains the Islamic beliefs in Allah, His angels, His revealed books, His messengers, the Day of Judgment, and divine predestination, presenting each belief with clarity and addressing common questions and misconceptions that beginners often have. The five pillars of Islam (the declaration of faith, prayer, fasting, charity, and pilgrimage) are each given a dedicated chapter that explains not only what each pillar entails but also why it matters spiritually and practically in the life of a Muslim. The section on the daily prayer (salah) includes step-by-step guidance on how to perform the prayer, what to recite, and the spiritual significance of each movement and recitation. Additional chapters cover topics that are essential for a complete understanding of Islam but are often overlooked in introductory texts, including the Islamic perspective on Jesus and Christianity, the role of women in Islam, the concept of jihad in its true meaning, Islamic ethics and moral values, the significance of the month of Ramadan, and the diversity of Muslim cultures and communities around the world. The book addresses common misconceptions about Islam directly and honestly, providing factual responses to the questions that non-Muslims most frequently ask. The writing style is engaging and personal, with the author's genuine warmth and enthusiasm for the subject making this guide both informative and enjoyable to read. This second edition has been revised and expanded with additional content reflecting contemporary discussions and questions about Islam.`,
