    slug: "khateeb-e-rasool-sabit-bin-qais",
    description: `Khateeb e Rasool Sabit Bin Qais (The Orator of the Messenger, Sabit ibn Qais) is a detailed Urdu-language biographical work that brings to life the story of Sabit ibn Qais ibn Shammas (may Allah be pleased with him), a distinguished companion of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) who was renowned as the most eloquent orator (khateeb) among the Muslims of Madinah. Sabit ibn Qais holds a unique position in the history of early Islam as the person who was appointed by the Prophet himself to deliver the Friday sermon (khutbah) on his behalf, making him the first official khateeb in Islamic history and setting a precedent for the institution of the Friday sermon that continues to this day in mosques around the world. The book traces his life from the pre-Islamic period, when he was known throughout Madinah for his unmatched eloquence and persuasive speaking ability, through his conversion to Islam and his subsequent role as one of the most prominent and active members of the Muslim community. The narrative includes the famous account of how Sabit ibn Qais, upon hearing the first verses of the Quran recited, immediately recognised the truth of Islam's message — a testimony to both the power of the Quran and the intellectual honesty of a man whose profession depended on the beauty of language. The book provides detailed accounts of his participation in the major events of early Islamic history, including the Battle of Badr, the Battle of Uhud, and the Battle of the Trench, where his skills as an orator and motivator of men were put to the service of the Muslim cause. His role as a mediator, advisor, and public representative of the Muslim community is discussed, showing how his communication skills served the ummah in times of both war and peace. The book also addresses a poignant episode in Sabit's life — his temporary withdrawal from public life due to a personal concern that was sensitively handled by the Prophet — and the lessons that this episode teaches about the Prophet's wisdom in dealing with the emotional needs of his companions. The later chapters discuss his legacy as the archetypal Muslim orator and the standards of eloquence, clarity, and sincerity that he established for the delivery of the Friday sermon and other public addresses in the Muslim community. Written in engaging Urdu with careful attention to historical accuracy, this biography sheds light on a companion whose contributions to Islamic civilisation deserve far greater recognition than they typically receive.`,
    metaDescription: "Khateeb e Rasool Sabit Bin Qais is a detailed Urdu biography of the Prophet's designated orator, a companion renowned for his eloquence and service."
