    slug: "kitab-at-tauhid-english-4-colour-17x24",
    description: `Kitab At-Tauhid (The Book of Monotheism) in this English-language four-colour edition is one of the most important and widely studied works on Islamic theology, authored by the eminent scholar Shaykh Muhammad ibn Abdul Wahhab (may Allah have mercy on him). This edition presents the complete text of this foundational work in English translation, printed in a striking four-colour format on a generous 17x24 centimetre page that enhances both readability and visual appeal. Kitab At-Tauhid is universally recognised as one of the most authoritative and comprehensive books ever written on the Islamic concept of Tawheed (the absolute oneness and uniqueness of Allah), which is the central pillar of Islamic faith and the foundation upon which all other beliefs and practices are built. The book systematically categorises the various aspects of Tawheed, beginning with Tawheed ar-Rububiyyah (the oneness of Allah's lordship — the belief that Allah alone is the Creator, Sustainer, and Controller of all existence), proceeding to Tawheed al-Uluhiyyah (the oneness of Allah's worship — the belief that Allah alone deserves to be worshipped and that all acts of worship must be directed exclusively to Him), and covering Tawheed al-Asma' was-Sifat (the oneness of Allah's names and attributes — the belief that Allah possesses the beautiful names and perfect attributes described in the Quran and hadith, without any distortion, denial, or comparison with created things). For each category, the author presents the relevant Quranic verses and hadith narrations that establish the correct Islamic belief, followed by a discussion of the ways in which this aspect of Tawheed has been violated throughout history, both by the pre-Islamic polytheists and by various groups within the Muslim community. The book identifies and refutes the major forms of shirk (associating partners with Allah) that have appeared throughout human history, including the worship of idols, the veneration of graves and saints as intermediaries, the use of talismans and amulets as sources of protection, the reliance on astrology and fortune-telling, and the attribution of divine powers to created beings. The four-colour printing format enhances the learning experience by using colour to distinguish between the main text, the Quranic verses, the hadith narrations, and the explanatory notes, making it easier for students and scholars to navigate and study the material. This edition is an essential resource for students of Islamic theology, teachers in Islamic schools and madrasahs, and any Muslim who wishes to develop a thorough understanding of the most fundamental concept in Islam.`,
    metaDescription: "Kitab At-Tauhid English 4-colour edition presents Shaykh Muhammad ibn Abdul Wahhab's authoritative work on Islamic monotheism in enhanced format."
