    slug: "loving-our-parents",
    description: `Loving Our Parents is a heartwarming and instructive English-language book that addresses one of the most emphasised obligations in Islam — the duty of children to love, honour, respect, and care for their parents. Drawing upon the Quran, the authentic hadith of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), and the inspiring examples from the lives of the companions and righteous predecessors, this book presents a comprehensive and practical guide to fulfilling the Islamic obligation of birr al-walidayn (kindness to parents) that goes far beyond mere obedience to encompass genuine love, emotional support, financial provision, physical care, and constant prayer for their well-being. The book opens with the powerful Quranic injunctions regarding parents, including the verse that pairs the command to worship Allah alone with the command to show kindness to parents, and the verse in which Allah instructs the believer to lower the wing of humility out of mercy to both parents, saying "My Lord, have mercy upon them as they brought me up when I was small." These verses are discussed with commentary that explains the depth and breadth of what Islam requires from children towards their parents, establishing that kindness to parents is one of the dearest deeds to Allah and one of the most heavily rewarded. The section on the hadith provides a rich collection of the Prophet's teachings about parents, including his statement that Paradise lies at the feet of mothers, his warning that the pleasure of Allah is contained in the pleasure of the father, and his instruction that a person's greatest deeds are still insufficient to repay a single night of the father's wakefulness caring for his child. The book addresses the practical aspects of caring for parents in their old age, including the emotional challenges of caregiving, the importance of patience and gentleness, the financial responsibilities of adult children, and the Islamic etiquette of interacting with elderly parents. Chapters are devoted to specific situations including caring for non-Muslim parents, dealing with difficult or demanding parents, maintaining the relationship after marriage, and the Islamic rulings on inheritance and wills. The book also addresses the emotional dimension of the parent-child relationship, discussing how to express love and gratitude, how to seek forgiveness for past mistakes, and how to cope with the loss of a parent. Written in clear, compassionate English, this book is essential reading for every Muslim who wishes to fulfil this sacred obligation with both faithfulness and heartfelt sincerity.`,
    metaDescription: "Loving Our Parents is an English Islamic guide on the duty of kindness, respect, and care for parents, with Quranic verses, hadith, and practical advice."
