    slug: "masnoon-namaz-aur-roz-marra-ki-duain-8x12",
    description: `Masnoon Namaz aur Roz Marra ki Duain is a compact and practical Urdu-language book in the 8x12 inch format that brings together two essential categories of Islamic devotional practice — the Prophetic prayers (salawat and nawafil) that go beyond the obligatory prayers, and the daily supplications (du'as) that the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) taught his companions to recite at various points throughout the day and night. The book is designed as a convenient daily companion that Muslims can keep at home, in the mosque, or carry with them, providing quick and easy access to the authentic supplications and prayers that form the spiritual backbone of a practicing Muslim's daily routine. The section on masnoon namaz (Prophetic prayers) covers all the supererogatory prayers that are confirmed from the Sunnah of the Prophet, including the rawatib (the regular sunnah prayers associated with each of the five obligatory prayers), the Tahajjud (the night prayer that the Prophet described as the prayer of the righteous), the Duha (the forenoon prayer), the Istikhara prayer (the prayer of seeking guidance), the prayer of need (salat al-hajah), the prayer for rain (salat al-istisqa'), the funeral prayer (salat al-janazah), and the Eid prayers. For each prayer, the book provides the method of performance, the number of rak'ahs, the recommended times, and the relevant supplications and Quranic recitations. The section on roz marra ki duain (daily supplications) presents a comprehensive collection of the du'as that the Prophet recommended for the various situations and occasions that a person encounters in the course of a normal day. These are organised according to the natural flow of daily life, beginning with the supplications for waking up in the morning, performing ablution, entering and leaving the home and mosque, the five daily prayers, eating and drinking, wearing new clothes, travelling, sleeping, and the general morning and evening adhkar. Each supplication is presented in clear Arabic text alongside its Urdu translation, and the references to the source hadith are provided for verification. The 8x12 inch format makes this book large enough for comfortable reading while remaining portable enough for regular daily use. The clear layout and systematic organisation make it easy to quickly find the desired prayer or supplication. This book is particularly useful for families who wish to establish the practice of daily adhkar in their homes, for students in madrasahs who are learning these essential devotions, and for anyone who wants a reliable reference for the authentic Prophetic prayers and supplications.`,
    metaDescription: "Masnoon Namaz aur Roz Marra ki Duain is a practical 8x12 Urdu book of authentic Prophetic prayers and daily supplications with Arabic text and Urdu meanings."
