    slug: "minhaj-ul-muslim-english-2-vols",
    description: `Minhaj Ul Muslim (The Methodology of the Muslim) in this two-volume English translation is one of the most comprehensive and widely respected works of contemporary Islamic scholarship, originally authored in Arabic by the eminent scholar Shaykh Abu Bakr al-Jaza'iri. This English translation brings the complete text of this monumental work to English-speaking Muslims, providing them with a detailed and systematic guide to the beliefs, practices, ethics, and daily life of a Muslim according to the Quran and the authentic Sunnah. The two volumes together cover virtually every aspect of Islamic life, making this work a complete reference library in a single set. The first volume focuses on the foundational matters of Islamic faith and worship, beginning with a thorough exposition of the six articles of faith (iman) — belief in Allah, His angels, His revealed books, His messengers, the Day of Judgment, and divine predestination — with detailed explanations supported by evidence from the Quran and hadith. The section on the five pillars of Islam provides comprehensive guidance on each pillar: the declaration of faith (shahadah) with an explanation of its meaning and implications; the five daily prayers (salah) with detailed instructions on how to perform them correctly, including the rulings on the conditions, pillars, and recommended acts of prayer; the obligatory fast of Ramadan (sawm) with guidance on the rules, virtues, and recommended practices of fasting; the obligatory charity (zakah) with detailed rulings on who must pay it, how much must be paid, and who is eligible to receive it; and the pilgrimage to Makkah (hajj) with a complete guide to the rites and rituals. The second volume covers the broader aspects of Islamic life, including Islamic ethics and moral conduct, covering topics such as honesty, truthfulness, patience, gratitude, humility, modesty, and kindness; the Islamic rulings on family life including marriage, divorce, inheritance, and the rights and responsibilities of husbands and wives; the Islamic approach to social life including the etiquette of greeting, visiting, eating, sleeping, and dressing; the Islamic perspective on contemporary issues such as work, education, health, and entertainment; and guidance on spiritual development including the recommended acts of worship, the remembrance of Allah (dhikr), and the pursuit of knowledge. The English translation maintains the scholarly precision and systematic organisation of the original Arabic text while using clear and accessible English that makes the material understandable to readers without advanced knowledge of Islamic terminology. These two volumes are an essential addition to the library of every English-speaking Muslim household and an invaluable resource for students and teachers of Islamic studies.`,
    metaDescription: "Minhaj Ul Muslim English 2-vol set by Shaykh Abu Bakr al-Jaza'iri is a comprehensive guide to Islamic faith, worship, ethics, and daily life."
