    slug: "mukhtasar-bayan-ul-quran-by-dr-israr-ahmed",
    description: `Mukhtasar Bayan Ul Quran (Brief Commentary on the Quran) by Dr Israr Ahmed is an abridged Urdu-language commentary (tafsir) on the Holy Quran by one of the most influential Islamic scholars and thinkers of the contemporary Muslim world. Dr Muhammad Israr Ahmed (1932-2010), the founder of the Tanzeem-e-Islami, devoted his life to the study and teaching of the Quran, and his complete multi-volume tafsir titled "Bayan Ul Quran" is widely regarded as one of the most significant Urdu-language tafsir works of the twentieth century. This mukhtasar (abridged) edition condenses the essential content of the complete work into a single accessible volume, making the core insights and explanations of Dr Israr Ahmed's Quranic commentary available to a broader audience. The commentary follows the traditional order of the Quranic surahs, providing for each surah a discussion of its background and context (asbab an-nuzul), its central themes and message, a verse-by-verse explanation of the key passages, and the practical lessons and implications that the surah holds for contemporary Muslims. Dr Israr Ahmed's approach to tafsir is distinguished by several characteristics that give this work its unique value. First, his emphasis on understanding the Quran as a unified, coherent message rather than as a collection of disconnected verses, showing how each surah contributes to the overall Quranic worldview. Second, his focus on the Quran's revolutionary social and political message, highlighting the Quran's call for the establishment of a just social order, the elimination of exploitation and oppression, and the creation of a society that lives in accordance with the guidance of Allah. Third, his thorough discussion of the philosophical and intellectual dimensions of Quranic teachings, addressing the deeper questions of human existence, the nature of good and evil, the meaning of history, and the relationship between faith and reason. Fourth, his consistent effort to connect the Quranic message to the contemporary situation of the Muslim ummah, showing how the Quranic guidance applies to the political, social, economic, and spiritual challenges that Muslims face in the modern world. The Urdu language used in the commentary is scholarly yet accessible, combining the precision of academic writing with the warmth and passion of a devoted student of the Quran. This abridged edition is an excellent starting point for readers who wish to benefit from Dr Israr Ahmed's Quranic insights without committing to the full multi-volume work, and serves as a valuable resource for students, teachers, and anyone who wishes to deepen their understanding of the Quran's message.`,
