    slug: "mukhtasar-riyad-us-saliheen-urdu",
    description: `Mukhtasar Riyad Us Saliheen (Abridged Gardens of the Righteous) in this Urdu-language edition is a concise collection of authentic hadith compiled from the famous Riyadh as-Salihin (Gardens of the Righteous) of Imam Yahya ibn Sharaf an-Nawawi (may Allah have mercy on him), one of the most celebrated hadith scholars in Islamic history. Imam Nawawi's Riyadh as-Salihin is one of the most widely read hadith collections in the Muslim world, cherished for its practical focus on the hadith that directly relate to the daily life, worship, ethics, and spiritual development of the individual Muslim. This mukhtasar (abridged) edition presents a carefully selected subset of the hadith from the original collection, chosen for their particular relevance to the needs of contemporary Muslims and arranged in a format that facilitates daily reading and reflection. The hadith are organised into thematic chapters that cover the major areas of Islamic practice and belief, including faith (iman) and its branches; the obligatory acts of worship including prayer, fasting, charity, and pilgrimage; the recommended acts of worship including voluntary prayers, remembrance of Allah (dhikr), supplication (du'a), and night prayer; moral character and ethical conduct including honesty, truthfulness, patience, gratitude, humility, forgiveness, kindness to parents, and good treatment of neighbours; social etiquette including the Islamic greeting, visiting the sick, attending funerals, and maintaining family ties; and spiritual development including the fear of Allah, hope in His mercy, repentance, and trust in His decree. Each hadith is presented in its original Arabic text with full vowel marks (tashkeel) for correct reading, followed by the Urdu translation and brief explanatory notes where necessary. The chain of narration (isnad) is provided for each hadith, allowing the reader to verify its authenticity, and the grading of the hadith is indicated where applicable. The Urdu translation is accurate and readable, conveying both the literal meaning and the spiritual depth of the Prophetic words. The abridgment has been carefully done to maintain the coherence and usefulness of the original collection while making it more manageable in size and more focused on the most essential hadith. This edition is particularly suitable for daily reading, as each chapter can be read in a short sitting, and the hadith provide continuous spiritual nourishment and practical guidance for the reader's daily life. It is an excellent companion for anyone who wishes to develop a closer relationship with the Sunnah of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him).`,
    metaDescription: "Mukhtasar Riyad Us Saliheen Urdu is an abridged hadith collection from Imam Nawawi covering faith, worship, ethics, and daily spiritual guidance."
