    slug: "muntakhab-qurani-waqiat",
    description: `Muntakhab Qurani Waqiat (Selected Quranic Events) is a valuable Urdu-language book that compiles and narrates the major events, stories, and historical accounts mentioned in the Holy Quran in a systematic and accessible format. The Quran is replete with narratives drawn from human history — the stories of the prophets and their peoples, accounts of ancient civilisations, descriptions of natural phenomena, and records of events that serve as lessons for all generations — and this book gathers the most significant of these events into a single, well-organised reference that allows the reader to understand the Quranic narratives in their proper context and sequence. The book is arranged thematically, with each major event or story receiving its own dedicated chapter that presents the complete Quranic account of the event, identifies all the verses across different surahs that relate to it, and provides relevant hadith narrations and scholarly commentary that explain the significance and lessons of the event. The section on the stories of the prophets (qasas al-anbiya) covers the narratives of all the prophets mentioned in the Quran, from Prophet Adam (peace be upon him) and the beginning of human history, through the stories of Prophet Nuh and the Great Flood, Prophet Ibrahim and his trials, Prophet Musa and the liberation of the Children of Israel, Prophet Dawud and Prophet Sulayman and their kingdoms, Prophet Isa and his miraculous birth and mission, and culminating with the comprehensive account of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) as presented across multiple surahs of the Quran. For each prophetic story, the book presents the Quranic verses in their original Arabic alongside the Urdu translation, allowing the reader to follow the narrative directly from the primary source. The section on the events of the early Muslim community covers the major episodes from the life of Prophet Muhammad as recorded in the Quran, including the revelation in the Cave of Hira, the migration to Madinah, the battles of Badr, Uhud, and the Trench, the Treaty of Hudaybiyyah, and the conquest of Makkah. The section on historical events from earlier civilisations covers the Quranic accounts of the people of Aad, Thamud, the Companions of the Cave, and other ancient peoples whose stories serve as warnings about the consequences of rejecting divine guidance. Written in clear, scholarly Urdu, this book is an excellent resource for understanding the narrative portions of the Quran and for appreciating the depth and richness of the Quranic storytelling tradition.`,
    metaDescription: "Muntakhab Qurani Waqiat is a systematic Urdu compilation of major events and stories from the Holy Quran with scholarly commentary and hadith references."
